EmailTemplate.name: TH 2013 - Pre-Trip Email
EmailTemplate.subject: All your need to know about your upcoming Thailand trip!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hey everyone!
Only 3 more months until we embark on our journey to Thailand! I hope everyone is excited and ready to go. This e-mail has a lot of useful information about our upcoming trip, so please read carefully.
1) Packing List - No idea what to pack? Read the attached document and it will remind you of all the little things that will make your trip and travels more comfortable.
2) Payment Deadline - March 1st, 2013 is when your fundraising money must be in our office. I hope everyone has been having great success with their fundraising!
3) The following items are for anyone 18 or older as of January 1, 2013:
Link to Back Check for Criminal Record Check - This is an online link to obtain a Criminal Record Check. All volunteers over 18 yrs old are required to complete a Criminal Record Check with a Vulnerable Sector Screening. Please e-mail me if you wish to be sent a link, you can also get a Criminal Record Check at your local police station, but sometimes, this can be a lot of hassle.
Child Protection Policy - This is for any volunteers over the age of 18 as of January 1st to read for each trip they attend. It is Live Different's Child Protection Policy. It is our policy on what is appropriate behaviour when dealing with minors and the steps that we take to protect them. It is important that you take the time to read this beginning to end.
Child Protection Policy Agreement - Once you have read the above Child Protection Policy, please sign the agreement and scan/email it back to me.
4) Flight Itinerary - Please book your flights and forward me the physical itinerary that your airlines have sent you.
5) Travel Insurance - After booking your travel insurance, please forward me the following information: Travel Insurance Provider, Policy #, and 2 phone numbers to call while you are travelling.
6) Trip Itinerary - The attached document is a rough copy of our schedule and is subject to change.
7) Creative Festival - You may notice that there are many days on our schedule allotted for Creative Festival.
We are really excited about what this is going to look like and are pretty sure that you are going to love being a part of it! The children's home we work with (www.yourbuddies.org) loves to provide opportunities, whenever possible, for the children to explore the arts and find freedom and healing through self expression.
They don't have a lot of teams visit them, and they have very few opportunities or resources to be able to explore the creative gifts that many of them possess. We want to help change that this year through hosting and experiencing a week long creative arts festival with them! We are going to be doing all kinds of great activities such as photography, video, painting, music and even possibly yoga with the staff and children.
The festival will run for 5 days, including a final wrap up party where they will perform and show off their creations. During that time, we will also be helping to complete a work project with the home to help upkeep the property and keep it safe for everyone. We will be doing the festival in the mornings and working on the project in the afternoons. We would love to have your input on the festival!
Christal is available to email any ideas you may have (christal@livedifferent.com). Don't worry about whether you feel creative or not! Each one of us can play a part in helping to bring healing to these kids and to helping to shape their future by investing in them during our time there.
Christal will be sending you more information as she works with the team in Thailand to shape and mold the festival.
8) Work Project - You may notice that there are many days on our schedule allotted for a Work Project.
We are currently working with the staff at the Children's Home to see what will be the best project for us to help them with while we are there. We will be able to solidify our plans closer to the date. Their needs are changing and evolving at the current time, and we want to make sure that we are able to make the most of our time with them and provide them with the best options possible. As soon as the project is solidified (probably by the end of February) you will be informed as to what more to expect.
9) Currency - Please feel free to bring Canadian Dollars and our staff members will go with you to exchange for a great rate. ABM's are also widely available. If you need to make any other arrangements, please contact us to check on the availability.
10) Extra Money - This is optional: souvenirs, snacks, extra help with gifts for the staff (suggested amount is $30)
11) Meals - We will be covering all meals during your time with us, from airport pickup to drop off at the end of the trip.
12) Sleepover at the Children's Homes - In shifts of 3 persons a night, we will have an opportunity step into the children's lives and stay with the staff at the home! This is an optional activity.
13) Laundry - There will be laundry days allotted where everyone can get their laundry done, it will cost roughly $6-7 CDN per "grocery-sized" bag.
14) Transportation - We will be travelling in a mini bus while we are there (a cross between mini van and a bus). Our driver's name is "Milk" (honestly!) and we have worked with him for four years. We are completely confident in his safety precautions and reliability.
15) T-shirt size - We will be providing Live Different t-shirts when you arrive in Thailand. Please tell me your t-shirt preference so I can pack accordingly.
Choose your style: v-neck or crew neck Choose you color: navy blue, dark grey, or light grey
16) Preparing for your time there - Here are 2 books that are a great read to prepare you for your trip.
Foreign to Familiar by Sarah A. Lanier Not for Sale by David Batstone.
17) Contact
Phone Number: with country code 011-6681-179-5013 and without country code 081-179-5013. This is JK's phone (our English speaking associate that we work with in Thailand). He is available on this number, and an alternate number will be sent out closer to our time of departure. Internet Access: wifi will be available at the hotel. Generally speaking, it is good enough to skype so you will be able to connect with friends and family back home
18) Blogs and Photos - Our facebook page will be updated each day so your family and friends can follow you throughout your trip!
http://www.facebook.com/pages/Live-Different/189864944417296
19) Baggage - Double check with your airlines on any luggage limitations, including number of checked bags.
20) Donations: The most helpful donation is always bringing cash to support the local economy. We will have a chance to shop for the children and fill up back packs full of items that are neccesities while we are there. It is so much fun!
Here is a list of items that you can bring down, please only bring what is listed:
children's art supplies and school supplies children's new underwear (from pre-school to teenagers) toys such as soccer balls, skipping ropes, bubbles, toy cars, dolls and teddy bears nice hygiene supplies for the staff who run the children's home (approximately 12 staff members, one third male and two thirds female) baby supplies such as baby blankets, toys, etc.
Please let me know if you have any questions and I will be happy to answer them!
Joy Yu
Programs Administrative Assistant
joy@livedifferent.com
